results.name: Coefficients in expansion of E_6^2/Product_{k>=1} (1-q^k)^24.
comment: Convolution square of A007242. - _Michael Somos_, Mar 31 2019
link: Vaclav Kotesovec, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000 (terms 0..1000 from Seiichi Manyama)
formula: a(n) = A000521(n-1) for n = 0 and n > 1.
G.f.: q * (j(q) - 1728) where j(q) is a modular function. - _Michael Somos_, Mar 31 2019
mathematica: nmax = 20; CoefficientList[Series[(1 - 504*Sum[DivisorSigma[5,k]*x^k, {k, 1, nmax}])^2 / Product[(1 - x^k)^24, {k, 1, nmax}], {x, 0, nmax}], x] (* _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Jul 09 2017 *)
a[ n_] := SeriesCoefficient[ q Series[ 1728 (KleinInvariantJ[Log[q] / (2 Pi I)] - 1), {q, 0, n}], {q, 0, n}]; (* _Michael Somos_, Mar 31 2019 *)
program: (PARI) {a(n) = my(A, U1, U2); if( n<0, 0, A = x * O(x^n); U1 = eta(x + A)^24; U2 = eta(x^2 + A)^24; polcoeff( (U1 - 512*x * U2)^2 * (U1 + 64*x * U2) / (U1^2 * U2), n))}; /* _Michael Somos_, Mar 31 2019 */
